zel|url=http://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2007/12/20071227-3.html|publisher=The White House|accessdate=2007-12-27|date=2007-12-27|archive-date=2011-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706180150/http://georgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov/news/releases/2007/12/20071227-3.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[美東時間|美東時間]]12月27日13:00的另一場記者會中，一位[[美國國務院|美國國務院]]發言人宣稱「巴基斯坦民主進程的任何延誤或落後，將會是應為布托遇刺負責的極端主義份子的勝利」，他並宣稱「繼續民主程序可能是解救極端主義的最佳良藥」。他要求一個「可信的、透明的」調查，並且暗示對於本事件「國際間廣泛的憤怒」。<ref>A press briefing with a [[United_States_Department_of_State|US State Department]] spokesman which was aired online as it occurred on {{cite news|title=CNN.com Live|url=http://www.cnn.com/video/live/live.html?stream=stream1|date=2007-12-27|accessdate=2007-12-27|archive-date=2007-12-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071227062314/http://www.cnn.com/video/live/live.html?stream=stream1|dead-url=no}}</ref>他並表示[[喬治·沃克·布希|喬治布殊]]總統在美東時間13:15與[[穆沙拉夫|穆沙拉夫]]通話。<ref>{{cite news |first=Tabassum |last=Zakaria |title=Bush has spoken with Musharraf: White House |url=http://www.boston.com/news/world/asia/articles/2007/12/27/bush_has_spoken_with_musharraf_white_house/ |publisher=The Boston Globe |date=2007-12-27 |accessdate=2007-12-27}}</ref>
